{"build_type":"executable","description":"Trivial executable that returns 42, used to verify the ELF writer chooser: built in default mode it is a static ET_EXEC (must exit 42, confirming the refactored emit_elf_image preserves the static layout byte-for-byte); built with elf:dynamic it is a position-independent ET_DYN/PIE (must also exit 42, confirming our PIC code runs when the kernel relocates it to an arbitrary base). PIE is the prerequisite ELF form for the PT_INTERP loader.","module_name":"return-integer-fortytwo-originating-inside-program","package_name":"return-integer-fortytwo-originating-inside-program","function_definitions":{"return-integer-fortytwo-originating-inside-program":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v42","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":42},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"v42"}}]}}}